{{Infobox video game |title = Chariot |image = Chariot game logo.png |developer = [[Frima Studio]] |publisher = Frima Studio |released = {{vgrelease|NA|30 September 2014|EU|1 October 2014}}'''Wii U'''{{Video game release|WW|8 January 2015}}'''Nintendo Switch'''{{Video game release|WW|May 10, 2018}} |genre = [[Puzzle video game|Puzzle]], [[platform game|platform]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]] |platform = [[Apple TV]], [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Nintendo Switch]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Wii U]], [[Xbox One]] }}
'''''Chariot''''' is a co-op [[platform game]] for the [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox One]], [[Wii U]] and [[Microsoft Windows]] developed and published by [[Frima Studio]], with the participation of the [[Canada Media Fund]]. It was first released on September 30, 2014 and was launched on Xbox One the next day as part of the Xbox Live Games with Gold program.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://news.xbox.com/2014/09/games-gwg-chariot-battlefield |title=Two Classics Back Up Chariot in October's Games with Gold |publisher=News.xbox.com |date=2014-09-25 |accessdate=2015-07-15}}</ref> An enhanced port entitled '''''Super Chariot''''' was released for the [[Nintendo Switch]] on May 10, 2018, and will include the Royal Gadget Pack DLC.<ref name="NL cites Switch release">{{cite news |last1=Vogel |first1=Mitch |title=Super Chariot Arrives On The Switch Later This Year |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/01/super_chariot_arrives_on_the_switch_later_this_year |work=[[Nintendo Life]] |date=16 January 2018 |accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref>
''Chariot'' differs from most traditional [[Platform game]] as the objective is to lug around an object, the Chariot, to the end of each level. To do so, the players have to use physics-based mechanics such as pushing and pulling, adding a layer of [[Puzzle video game|Puzzle]] to the game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chariotgame.com/faq/ |title=FAQ : Chariot |publisher=Chariot Game |date= |accessdate=2015-07-15}}</ref>
==Plot== ''Chariot'' chronicles a princess' quest to fulfill her recently deceased father's final wishes and bury him in peace. As might be expected of royalty, his last request is that he be laid to rest with as much wealth as possible.<ref name="destructoid1">{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/review-chariot-281861.phtml |title=Review: Chariot |publisher=Destructoid.com |date= |accessdate=2015-07-15}}</ref>
==Gameplay== The entire game can be played solo or with a partner. The king's body is in a coffin and attached to it are four wheels. The player's character can push the chariot up and down small hills or attach a rope to pull it along. The rope can be extended or shortened to adequately maneuver the chariot throughout the environment. Everything behaves as it should, with real physics playing a big part in how things move.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaming-age.com/2015/01/chariot-review-wii-u/|title=Chariot review for Wii U|publisher=Gaminga-age.com|accessdate=2015-07-15}}</ref>
==Reception== On [[Metacritic]], ''Chariot'' scores an average metascore of 76 on [[PlayStation 4]], [[Wii U]] and [[Personal computer|PC]] and 73 on [[Xbox One]].{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} It achieved a 8.5 from [[Destructoid]], as "a memorable game that's hard not to like and recommend to others."<ref name="destructoid1"/>
