{{Infobox video game | title = Deep Rock Galactic | developer = Ghost Ship Games | publisher = [[Coffee Stain Publishing]] | engine = [[Unreal Engine 4]] | platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Xbox One]] | genre = [[First-person shooter]] | modes = [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]], [[single-player]] }}
'''''Deep Rock Galactic''''' is a [[cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] [[first-person shooter]] [[video game]] developed by Danish indie studio Ghost Ship Games and published by Coffee Stain Publishing. It released on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] in Early Access and [[Xbox One]] Preview on February 28, 2018 and is developed in [[Unreal Engine 4]].<ref name=Polygon>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/2/28/17064132/deep-rock-galactic-steam-xbox-one-price-release-date-early-access|title=Deep Rock Galactic is the best new co-op shooter on Steam and Xbox One| publisher=Polygon | author=Charlie Hall| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2018/02/14/deep-rock-galactic-coming-soon-xbox-one-windows-10/|title=Deep Rock Galactic Arrives on Xbox One and Windows 10 This Month| publisher=Xbox | author=Mikkel Martin Pedersen| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/live-out-your-dwarf-bothering-fantasies-well-most-of-them-with-deep-rock-galactic-at-the-pc-gamer-weekender/|title=Live out your dwarf-bothering fantasies (well, most of them) with Deep Rock Galactic at the PC Gamer Weekender| publisher=GamesRadar| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=http://comicbook.com/gaming/2018/02/14/deep-rock-galactic-early-access-game-preview/|title=Deep Rock Galactic Comes to Early Access, Game Preview This Month| publisher=Comic Book| author=TANNER DEDMON | accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref>
==Gameplay== ''Deep Rock Galactic'' is a 1-4 player [[cooperative gameplay|cooperative]]<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.vg247.com/2018/03/09/deep-rock-galactic-early-access-review/|title=Deep Rock Galactic is a fresh take on co-op shooters with tangible depth and a lot of character| publisher=VG247 | author= Sherif Sae| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref> [[first-person shooter]] [[video game]] where players work together while exploring procedurally generated cave systems.<ref name=RPS>{{cite web |url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/03/19/how-deep-rock-galactic-mines-fun-from-absolute-darkess/|title=How Deep Rock Galactic mines fun from absolute darkness| publisher=Rock Paper Shotgun |date=March 19, 2018 | author=Alex Wiltshire| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref>
Players take on the role of space dwarves assigned to mine minerals in dark caves on the planet Hoxxes IV.<ref name=Polygon/><ref name=RPS/> The main antagonists are swarms of alien arachnids called Glyphids.<ref name=Polygon/><ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/deep-rock-galactics-left-4-dead-like-mining-adventures-make-it-the-ideal-early-access-game/|title=Deep Rock Galactic's Left 4 Dead-like mining adventures make it the ideal Early Access game| publisher=PC Gamer | author= James Davenport| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.unrealengine.com/en-US/blog/guns-gold-and-glory-in-the-caverns-of-deep-rock-galactic/|title=Guns, Gold, and Glory in the Caverns of Deep Rock Galactic| publisher=Unreal Engine| author=Shawn Petraschuk| accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref> One reviewer described it as "a mix of [[Minecraft]] and [[Left 4 Dead]]".<ref name=RPS/>
== Classes == Currently there are four playable classes to choose from. They're all unique and have a certain playstyle. Players can choose classes while in the main lobby by using once of the computers that are inside the rooms.
=== Engineer === The engineer has a shotgun, a grenade launcher, the ability to build up to 2 sentry guns and a platform gun that shoots walkable platforms.
=== Gunner === A soldier/ heavy class that is equipped with a minigun and a pistol. He also has access to a satchel charge that works like a detonation packet. He also has a zipline gun that shoots ziplines that can be used by all.
=== Driller === A miner class, the driller is equipped with power drills, which mines much faster than a pickaxe. He is also equipped with a flamethrower, a pistol and a satchel charge.
=== Scout === A class that is meant to get to places, the scout is equipped with an assault rifle, a shotgun and a grappling gun. He is important to have in the team since he also has the flare gun, which flares shine brighter and longer than the normal flares.
