{{Infobox video game |title= |image=Drawrace2 boxart.jpg |caption=''DrawRace 2 HD'' application icon |developer=[[RedLynx]] |publisher=[[Chillingo]] |series=''DrawRace'' |released=September 1, 2011 |genre=[[racing game|racing]] |modes=[[Single-player]], [[multiplayer]] |platforms=[[iOS]] }}
'''''DrawRace 2''''' is a [[racing game|racing]] [[video game]] developed by [[RedLynx]] and published by [[Chillingo]]. It was released September 1, 2011 for [[iOS]] devices, and serves as the sequel to [[DrawRace]]. It is played by drawing an [[Racing line|ideal racing line]] on the game's screen with a finger. The car then follows this line during a race. The game was well received by critics, and holds a four stars rating and an average score of 88/100 at review aggregator [[Metacritic]].
==Gameplay== [[File:Drawrace2 screenshot.jpg|thumb|left|In ''DrawRace 2'' the player creates a driving path for their vehicle (shown in red) with their finger prior to each race. Their car then follows that path during the race.]] ''DrawRace 2'' is a [[racing game]] in which the player predetermines their vehicle's route around a given track by drawing an [[racing line|ideal racing line]]. The entire course is seen from a top down perspective, similar to the 1986 arcade game ''[[Super Sprint]]''. The game includes 30 tracks, 16 cars and 180 challenges for players to complete. Leaderboards and leagues are also included. Multiplayer can be played with 2-4 players.<ref name="kotaku preview">{{Cite web |url=http://kotaku.com/5822977/the-next-big-racer-from-the-folks-behind-trials-hd |publisher=[[Kotaku]] |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=The Next Big Racer From the Folks Behind Trials HD |date=July 20, 2011 |first=Brian |last=Crecente}}</ref>
It differs from most top-down racers in that players use their finger to draw the route their car will take for all given laps. Players can draw faster or slower to have the car accelerate and brake once the race begins. Once all laps are drawn by the player the race begins, and the player's vehicle will follow the drawn path, taking into account the speed at which the player drew the route.<ref name="gamezebo preview">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamezebo.com/games/drawrace-2/preview |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |publisher=[[GameZebo]] |date=May 20, 2011 |first=Mike |last=Thompson |title=DrawRace 2 Preview}}</ref> During the actual race players can control a turbo boost button to give their car an increase in speed. This boost recharges over time.<ref name="kotaku preview" />
==Development and marketing== ''DrawRace 2'' was released September 1, 2011 for [[iOS]] devices.<ref name="press 1">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/76685/DrawRace_2_Swing_.. |publisher=[[Gamasutra]] |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |date=September 1, 2011 |title=DrawRace 2, Swing the Bat, and Fruit Roll}}</ref> On November 8, 2011 a free version entitled ''DrawRace 2 Free Multiplayer'' was released. The version includes 2-4 player gameplay, three tracks and three cars.<ref name="press multi">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/79510/Now_You_Can_Try_DrawRace_2_For_FreeRedLynx_and_Chillingorelease_DrawRace_2_Free_Multiplayer_for_iOS.php |publisher=Gamasutra |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |date=November 8, 2011 |title=Now You Can Try DrawRace 2 For FreeRedLynx and Chillingo release DrawRace 2 Free Multiplayer for iOS.}}</ref>
==Reception== {{Video game reviews |compilation = yes <!--AGGREGATE SCORES--> |MC = 88/100<ref name="mc" /> <!--REVIEWS--> |Edge = 9/10<ref name="edge review" /> |EuroG = 9/10<ref name="eurogamer review" /> |VG = 8/10<ref name="videogamer review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.videogamer.com/iphone/drawrace_2/review.html |first=Martin |last=Gaston |date=September 27, 2011 |publisher=[[videogamer.com]] |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=DrawRace 2 Review}}</ref> |rev1 = ''[[Gamezebo]]'' |rev1Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name="gamezebo review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamezebo.com/games/drawrace-2/review |first=Jim |last=Squires |date=September 6, 2011 |title=DrawRace 2 Review |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |publisher=GameZebo}}</ref> |rev2 = ''AppSpy'' |rev2Score = 5/5<ref name="appspy review" /> |rev3 = ''Slide to Play'' |rev3Score = 4/4<ref name="slidetoplay review" /> }}
''DrawRace 2'' received mostly positive reviews from critics. The game holds a score of 88/100 at [[Metacritic]].<ref name="mc">{{Cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/drawrace-2/critic-reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=DrawRace 2 Critic Reviews for iPhone/iPad at Metacritic.com}}</ref> The site also reports five media outlets gave the game perfect scores: AppSpy,<ref name="appspy review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.appspy.com/drawrace-2-review |publisher=AppSpy |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |date=September 1, 2011 |first=Andrew |last=Nesvadba |title=DrawRace 2 review}}</ref> Slide to Play,<ref name="slidetoplay review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/story/drawrace-2-review |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=DrawRace 2 Review |date=September 12, 2011 |first=Andrew |last=Webster |publisher=Slide to Play}}</ref> AppSmile,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.appsmile.com/2011/09/03/drawrace-2-review/ |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |publisher=AppSmile |date=September 3, 2011 |author=Kevin |title=DrawRace 2 Review}}</ref> TouchGen,<ref>{{Cite web |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |url=http://www.touchgen.net/drawrace-2-review |title=DrawRace 2 review |publisher=TouchGen |first=Torbjorn |last=Kamblad |date=September 3, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512022204/http://www.touchgen.net/drawrace-2-review |archivedate=May 12, 2012 |df= }}</ref> and Vandal Online.<ref>{{Cite web |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |url=http://www.vandal.net/analisis/iphone/drawrace-2-racing-evolved/14345 |publisher=Vandal Online |date=November 30, 2011 |title=DrawRace 2: Racing Evolved |author=Velocidad}}</ref> The lowest score came from PocketGamer France's reviewer, who gave the game a 68% approval rating.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pocketgamer.fr/test-jeu-iphone/10573-drawrace-2.html |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |publisher=PocketGamer France |author=bilaaa |date=September 12, 2011 |title=Test de DrawRace 2}}</ref> The game was the top seller the week of its release in several European countries, and placed in the top ten in more than 45 countries.<ref name="sales">{{Cite web |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |url=http://www.mcvuk.com/press-releases/read/drawrace-2-racing-to-1/084243 |publisher=mcvuk.com |date=September 5, 2011 |author=Games Press |title=DrawRace 2 Racing to #1}}</ref> [[Videogamer.com]] listed it in their Top Racing Games of 2011,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.videogamer.com/top-games/racing-games-2011/2/ |publisher=videogamer.com |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=Top Racing Games of 2011}}</ref> and ''[[Game Informer]]'' listed it in their "20 Mobile Games You Should Be Playing" feature.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2011/10/11/mobile-games-supplement.aspx |publisher=''[[Game Informer]]'' |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=20 Mobile Games You Should Be Playing Supplement |date=October 11, 2011 |first=Jeff |last=Marchiafava}}</ref>
GameZone's Andrew Hayward said "''DrawRace 2'' melds racing and strategy in a unique and iPad-centric sort of way".<ref name="gamezone review">{{Cite web |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |publisher=GameZone |url=http://www.gamesradar.com/ipad-reviews-week-vidrhythm-radballs-drawrace-2-serious-sam-kamikaze-attack/?page=2 |title=iPad reviews of the week: VidRhythm, Radballs, DrawRace 2, Serious Sam: Kamikaze Attack! |date=September 17, 2011 |first=Andrew |last=Hayward}}</ref> He further stated that while the control scheme probably would not "evolve the racing genre", it worked well for touchscreen devices.<ref name="gamezone review" /> In [[Metro.co.uk|''Metro'']]'s review of the game critic Roger Hargreaves called it "the most addictive and enjoyably infuriating turn-based game of the year."<ref name="metro review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.metro.co.uk/tech/games/875208-drawrace-2-review-micro-machines |publisher=[[Metro.co.uk|''Metro'']] |first=Roger |last=Hargreaves |date=September 12, 2011 |accessdate=May 15, 2012 |title=DrawRace 2 review – micro machines}}</ref> Hargreaves cited the large amount of content, multiplayer features, and presentation as high points of the game.<ref name="metro review" /> Toby Moses of ''[[Guardian.co.uk|The Guardian]]'' also praised the game. He stated that it was an improvement over the original ''DrawRace'', and felt that it "could well be the must-have app of the year."<ref name="guardian review">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2011/sep/11/new-apps-drawrace2-review |publisher=''[[Guardian.co.uk|The Guardian]]'' |first=Toby |last=Moses |date=September 10, 2011 |accessdate=May 15, 2012 |title=New apps: DrawRace2 – review}}</ref>
Slide to Play's Andrew Webster felt the game was a major improvement over its predecessor. He called it "a more fleshed out and expansive experience".<ref name="slidetoplay review" /> [[Eurogamer]]'s Kristan Reed thoroughly enjoyed the game &mdash; so much so that it prompted a change the site's mobile review format. Previously all reviewed games were covered under a blanket feature known as Mobile Games Roundup. Reed stated that in the new format highly rated games would not be limited to a small review, but in the future "games as brilliant as ''DrawRace 2'' [will now] on will get the extra depth they deserve."<ref name="eurogamer review">{{Cite web |accessdate=May 10, 2012|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2011-09-12-mobile-games-roundup-review?page=3 |date=September 12, 2011 |first=Kristan |last=Reed |title=Mobile Games Roundup • Page 3 |publisher=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref> He further noted that the price-to-value ratio was extremely high, and even jokingly stated that players should send RedLynx additional money past the purchase to make up for the value.<ref name="eurogamer review" /> The critic from ''[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]'' magazine called it the "exceptional sequel to the iOS racing line racer." The reviewer further noted that though the original ''DrawRace'' was good, the sequel "makes it look like an amateur effort."<ref name="edge review">{{Cite web |url=http://www.edge-online.com/reviews/drawrace-2-review |publisher=''[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]'' |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |title=DrawRace 2 review |date=September 8, 2011 |author=Edge staff}}</ref> {{-}}
