{{about|a lottery|golden kiwifruit|Kiwifruit}}

[[File:golden kiwi ticket.jpg|right|thumb|100px|$1,000,000 was the highest ever Golden Kiwi prize]]
'''Golden Kiwi''' was a [[New Zealand]] [[lottery]] which began in 1961 and ended in 1989. It was based on philanthropic art union lotteries held for many decades prior.<ref>[http://www.teara.govt.nz/1966/L/Lotteries/GoldenKiwiLottery/en Golden Kiwi Lottery] in ''An Encyclopaedia of New Zealand'', 1966</ref> It came under the authority of the [[New Zealand Lotteries Commission]] when the Commission was established in 1987 to run the new lottery.<ref>[http://www.nzlotteries.co.nz/wps/wcm/myconnect/lotteries2/nzlotteries/Global/AboutNZLotteries/History/# History], [[New Zealand Lotteries Commission|NZ Lotteries]]</ref> Golden Kiwi ended in 1989 with the introduction of the Instant Kiwi [[scratchcard|scratch card]] lottery.

