{{NewZealand-stub}}

The '''Hunnia Film Studio''' was the largest and most important [[film studio]] in [[Hungary]]. Located in the capital [[Budapest]], it was for many years under [[state ownership]]. It originally belonged to [[Alexander Korda]]'s [[Corvin Film]] company. In the closing months of the [[Second World War]] Hungary's ruling [[Arrow Cross Party|Arrow Cross]] regime planned to dismantle the studio and move it westwards, but this plan was wrecked when the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Red Army]] captured [[Budapest]] and took control of the studio.<ref>Cunningham p.60</ref>
It should not be confused with the earlier similarly named [[Hunnia Studio]].
