{{Infobox racecourse |name = Cherokee Casino Will Rogers Downs |image = |location = [[Rogers County, Oklahoma|Rogers County]], United States |owner = [[Cherokee Nation]] |opened = |coursetype = [[Thoroughbred]] [[flat racing]] & [[Quarter Horse]] racing |website = http://www.cherokeecasino.com/will-rogers-downs/ |notableraces = [[Clem McSpadden Memorial Route 66 Stakes]] }}
Cherokee Casino Will Rogers Downs is a gaming facility and horse racing track located in [[Rogers County, Oklahoma|Rogers County]], near [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]] and just east of [[Justice, Oklahoma|Justice]]). The track is owned and operated by the [[Cherokee Nation]].
[[Quarter Horse]] races are held September through November. [[Thoroughbred]] horse racing takes place from March through May. The track also features [[Appaloosa]] and [[American Paint Horse|Paint]] races.
The facility features a 2,700-seat grandstand along a one-mile long track.<ref name="Will Rogers Downs">{{cite web | url= http://www.cherokeecasino.com/will_rogers_downs/overview.aspx | title= Overview of Will Rogers Downs | publisher= Cherokee Nation | accessdate=2007-06-16}}</ref> The facility's casino section has 250 electronic gaming machines. Also on the grounds of the Downs complex is the largest [[recreational vehicle|RV]] park in Oklahoma. <ref name="Will Rogers Downs" />
